16832270.text:
** ``jv_table_information``**
This variable will be used to iterate the table creation.
If you have multiple tables, then put it in array in table_information.
Only put the table name as the table name that you put in Ingestion Metadata.
Example:
Instead "T_SOURCE_TABLE_NAME", just put "TABLE_NAME"

Put the s3_prefix including the regex expression based on Matillion's standard.
Example:
if you want to process all the files in the s3_path folder that has name starts with "file_name_prefix", then put .*/file_name_prefix.*

* delete_source_file_flag = TRUE / FALSE
By default is TRUE - it will delete the files in the S3 bucket.
Set as FALSE if you don't want to delete the files in the S3 bucket - for example, it's not your S3 bucket and the files are used for other projects.

JSON Structure:
{
    "table_information": [
        {
            "table_name": "TABLE_NAME",
            "s3_prefix": ".*/file_name_prefix.*"
            "table_columns": [
                {
                    "column_name": "COLUMN_NAME",
                    "column_type": "COLUMN_TYPE"
                }
                // Additional columns as needed
            ]
        }
        // Additional tables as needed
    ], 
     "file_type": "csv"
    , "csv_config": {
        "delimiter": ";",
        "header": "1"
    },
"delete_source_file_flag": "TRUE"
}

Default file type will be csv, with comma delimiter and with header.

